HEADWORD: Cynoscephalae
<hw>Cynoscephalae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the battle that
ended the second Macedonian War (197 BC); the Romans defeated King
Philip of Macedon.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> battle of Cynoscephalae.</syn>⟦br⟧
